title: For Sale:  Romanian AK47
postcontent:
Late 80s import. 
1.) DC Industries product: better than AK Waser 10 but not many DC rifles and not for the same price. 
2.) The very large oval dimple in the side of the slide indicates a pre ban receiver. It's designed to hold a double stack mag as opposed to other models which were modified after the Brady Ban expired requiring internal welding and such.
3.) The gas tube is aligned with the barrel the rifle, not warped due to excessive heating. Similarly for the sight.
4.) the muzzle is not welded on, interchangeable. 
5.) It comes w a standard mag but I also have a 40 round Bulgarian RPK47 mag which is far better quality then a similar Tempco or other cheap manufacturer. 
6.) A minor detail here is a Chinese handle grip. In order for these and some other firearms to be imported they have to have at least 4 American parts on them, 1 typically being the grip so this is considerd a minor mod. 
7.) lastly it comes w approx 40 rounds.
Perfect condition, no marks, scratches, or rust.
